attachments.fallback: [December 7th, 2016 7:03 AM] garisingh: <@U3B2F5VC0> - what are you trying to do?  there are currently 2 version of Fabric in play - V1 which is the current master branch and V0.6 which is in the v0.6 branch (and we have also published docker images to dockerhub under the hyperledger organization).  If your goal is to start learning chaincode, then for now I would recommend the v0.6 Docker images and following Option 2 or 3 from <http://hyperledger-fabric.readthedocs.io/en/latest/Setup/Chaincode-setup/>  .  If you want to be on the bleeding edge, things will unfortunately be  little tricky with the current master branch (we should have things a bit smoother over the course of the next week or so)
